# Join the Band Dance Party!

Band and Code.org believe in the power of computer science education for every student, in every classroom around the world. That’s why we’re teaming up to inspire students everywhere to code and dance — let’s celebrate the magic of computer science and music! 

Join the party by using Code.org’s Dance Party activity to code your own choreography to Band's “Song.” Get creative with classic moves, and have fun with new album-inspired visuals and dancer formations!

Post or submit your creations for Band and Code.org to see, and we’ll share the best ones on social media. Plus, you’ll get a chance to win tickets to see Band on tour, or a chance for your classroom to video chat with the band.

We can’t wait to see and share what you create! 


## How to join the fun — code, dance, and share!
<ol>
<li>Start <a href="https://code.org/dance">Dance Party</a></li>
<li>Learn to code your own dance in a short 10-step tutorial</li>
<li>On the final level, code an awesome dance to Band's song, “Song.” (Don’t forget to try out the special “Song” background effect!)</li>
<li>Click “Finish” to get a share link to your project.</li>
<li>For extra fun, make a video of yourself dancing along with your code!</li>
</ol>

